Fuck.
This has been a three-day ritual. We want to be here for her when my mom dies. She is finally succumbing to her Alzheimer's. I've spent two and a half years watching whatever was left of my mom disappear. Her memories of me and her beloved grandchild.
She didn't remember who we were. She knew that she loved us. That's something.
But the past three days have been either of her clutching at the sky in anxiety or fear or pain, or so drugged up that there can be no thoughts left.
And I don't know. Maybe there's some of her left in there.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/z0KPPb8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>To imagine some consciousness left in her mind...some comprehension as she struggles on her last breaths of life. If any part of her is still in there, she would be scared out of her mind. At no point in the last year has she really had any idea of what was going on.
What's the point of this? Dogs get a simple shot and that's it. There is zero percent chance of her ever coming back. Zero.
Soon, they say.

edit: Thank you, everyone. I don't have words right now.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NODGz8N</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DogsThatGoMoo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I don't know where else to put this, or if anybody cares.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bB3SQWu</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4PK58S6.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>For the past 9 years, I've had body image issues brought on by my being overweight. 9 years ago, I weighed 150 pounds. A year ago, I was 210. I'm 5'4". But when I looked down in the shower, all I could see was my extended stomach, for I don't know how many years. For the past 4 months, I've been biking to and from work due to an accident. This is the first time I've noticed any sort of weight loss, and I think it's the only thing that could have tipped me off that any weight was being lost as we don't own a scale.

 Before this, I wasn't really active, and I half-heartedly set an unrealistic goal of 10,000 steps a day to try to get me to try to achieve it. I think i achieved it twice in the 4 years since i set that goal. Along with biking 5 days a week and me working at a warehouse store, I'm now reaching that target almost daily that I work. 

It's an electric bike, it does most of the work, but it's working. It's only 4 miles there and back, but it's working. Losing weight wasn't an intention of getting a bike, it was only to be able to get to work and home reliably.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bB3SQWu</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[whybother]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>This</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ynpASW8</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Fyn2cEm.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ynpASW8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[stopfGemBaron]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>An important distinction ....</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/weDqgjv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/CYk6YNL.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Noam Chomsky</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/weDqgjv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[blank666man]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Like a black fly.. in a blue chardonnay</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/34jLt82</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nyKbdV0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/34jLt82</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Capinron]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Images of Note: Have a Fungus</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Hgom5KU</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BWRBquZ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xGI2P3i.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Hey City Council, Linux Mint will save you so much money</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/silxgik.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img al